                           <p>Upper part of a <material>white marble</material>
                              <objectType>panel-stele</objectType> (<height unit="metre">0.45</height> x <width unit="metre">0.46</width> x <depth unit="metre">0.16</depth>) broken below and chipped on all edges. The relief, which is broken at the waist, is of a facing <rs type="decoration">gladiator</rs>, with his head turned slightly to his right. He wears a highly decorated cuirass, with a rose and other designs on it in relief, and a decorated belt. On his left arm he holds a long shield with a decorated rim and the letter Γ in the top right corner. His right arm has an arm guard on the upper arm, which is all that survives. In the field on either side of the head are two wreaths, each decorated with a ribbon.</p>
